posts.title: If you believe that God saved President Trump from a would-be assassin’s bullet, as I do, then it’s easy to think that His purpose was for him to be re-elected. I would caution anyone against making that assumption.
posts.content:
You might be wondering why I’m even posting this here - well the truth of the matter is, I have no one else to share it with. So if this isn’t for you, then downvote and move on to the next post.

Anyway, I was thinking about this yesterday, as I watched clips of JD Vance deftly handling the press. Would Trump have picked him if he hadn’t had that experience in Pennsylvania? We know that Vance was being considered dating back to at least February, thanks to that leak from the “Iranians”, but maybe Trump’s near-death experience strengthened his resolve to make the choice. Maybe this all a setup for 2028.

Or, maybe this has nothing to do with the country at all and is about Trump’s personal relationship with God. Perhaps this gives him a perspective that he never had before, or an ounce of humility that he needed for his time here on Earth. We just don’t know.

The point is that, as much as we might want to believe otherwise, President Trump’s election is not guaranteed. We have to put in the work to make it happen. I do think this is a fight between good and evil, and the soul of our country hangs in the balance. Absolutely nothing good could come from a Harris/Walz administration: Even the people they purport to care about will suffer under their watch.

Keep praying for President Trump, his family, and his team. But do the work. If God gave you the ability to make a difference, then the time is now.
